<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 4:01PM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Brief heavy snowfall through 6 PM...
A band of heavy snowfall will continue for areas roughly south and
east of a Lake Zurich to Waukegan line through approximately 6 PM.
Snowfall rates within this band will briefly exceed an inch per
hour leading to rapid accumulations on roadways and sharply
reduced visibilities. Motorists are advised to use caution,
especially in the southeastern half of the county.</description>
